The paper deals with developing an end-to-end training algorithm for breast cancer diagnosis based on mammograms. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for training the model, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) for medical diagnosis, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of mammograms, which is a type of medical imaging, and therefore falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques for transferring the model to a different dataset, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
